  <FlashCard id="fc-equilibrium-vs-attractor">
    <Front>What is the difference between an equilibrium point and an attractor?</Front>
    <Back>An equilibrium (fixed point) is any state where f(x*) = 0. An attractor is an equilibrium (or limit cycle, strange attractor) that nearby trajectories converge to. Not all equilibria are attractors - unstable equilibria repel nearby trajectories.</Back>
  </FlashCard>

  <FlashCard id="fc-time-constant">
    <Front>In the passive membrane model, what is the membrane time constant tau and what does it determine?</Front>
    <Back>tau = C/g_L where C is membrane capacitance and g_L is leak conductance. It determines how quickly the membrane voltage responds to perturbations - larger tau means slower exponential return to rest.</Back>
  </FlashCard>

